<body><p>GE.14-12687 
</p>
<p>*1412687* 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-fifth session 
</b>Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Algeria, Bahrain,<footnote name="*">Non-member State of the Human Rights Council.  </footnote> Russian Federation, South Africa, United Arab Emirates: 
amendment to draft resolution A/HRC/25/L.18/Rev.1 
</b></p>
<p><b>  25/&#8230;  Adequate housing as a component of the right to an adequate 
standard of living 
</b></p>
<p>After paragraph 3, insert two new paragraphs <i>reading</i>  
</p>
<p>3.bis <i>Urges</i> States to recognize the effect that discrimination, marginalization and 
social exclusion have had and continue to have on many racial groups living in a 
numerically based minority situation within a State, to ensure that persons in such groups 
can exercise, as individual members of such groups, fully and effectively, all human rights 
and fundamental freedoms without distinction and in full equality before the law, and to 
take, where applicable, appropriate measures with regard to employment, housing and 
education with a view to preventing racial discrimination; 
</p>
<p>3.ter <i>Also urges</i> States to take, where applicable, appropriate measures to prevent 
racial discrimination against persons belonging to national or ethnic, religious and linguistic 
minorities with regard to housing and related social services; 
</p>
<p>    
</p>
